BTW, just tested icc and icc doesn't generate cld either (so it matches the
new gcc behavior).
char buf1[32], buf2[32];
void bar (void);
void foo (void)
{
  __builtin_memset (buf1, 0, 32);
  bar ();
  __builtin_memset (buf2, 0, 32);
}
